"use strict";(self.webpackChunkdocs=self.webpackChunkdocs||[]).push([[759],{4759:(i,e,t)=>{t.r(e),t.d(e,{default:()=>a});const a='<h2 id="more-demos-and-examples">More Demos and Examples</h2>\n<p><a href="javascript:document.dispatchEvent(new CustomEvent(\'routeTo\', {detail: \'/angular/demos\'})); void(0)">Angular</a></p>\n<p><a href="javascript:document.dispatchEvent(new CustomEvent(\'routeTo\', {detail: \'/react/demos\'})); void(0)">React</a></p>\n<p><a href="javascript:document.dispatchEvent(new CustomEvent(\'routeTo\', {detail: \'/svelte/demos\'})); void(0)">Svelte</a></p>\n<p><a href="javascript:document.dispatchEvent(new CustomEvent(\'routeTo\', {detail: \'/solid-js/demos\'})); void(0)">SolidJS</a></p>\n<h2 id="stateadapts-purpose">StateAdapt&#39;s Purpose</h2>\n<p>Features should naturally evolve in a declarative manner to support unpredictable business requirements.\nSimple features should not need heavy syntax to be declarative,\nand adding complexity should not require drastic refactors.</p>\n<p>Declarative code is when declarations are complete. Rather than requiring scattered imperarive code, declarative code is reactive.</p>\n<p>Declarative code has many benefits:</p>\n<ul class="bx--list--ordered"><li class="bx--list__item"><a href="https://dev.to/mfp22/rxjs-can-save-your-codebase-49fi#focus">Focus</a></li><li class="bx--list__item"><a href="https://dev.to/mfp22/rxjs-can-save-your-codebase-49fi#debugging-with-context">Debugging with Context</a></li><li class="bx--list__item"><a href="https://dev.to/mfp22/rxjs-can-save-your-codebase-49fi#avoiding-bugs-with-context">Avoiding Bugs with Context</a></li><li class="bx--list__item"><a href="https://dev.to/mfp22/rxjs-can-save-your-codebase-49fi#comprehensibility">Comprehensibility</a></li><li class="bx--list__item"><a href="https://dev.to/mfp22/rxjs-can-save-your-codebase-49fi#declarativeness-in-rxjs-vs-signals-only">Separation of Concerns / Colocation</a></li><li class="bx--list__item"><a href="https://dev.to/this-is-learning/5-reasons-to-avoid-imperative-code-e09#1-inconsistent-state">Consistent State</a></li><li class="bx--list__item"><a href="https://dev.to/this-is-learning/5-reasons-to-avoid-imperative-code-e09#2-state-elevation">State Locality</a></li><li class="bx--list__item"><a href="https://dev.to/this-is-learning/5-reasons-to-avoid-imperative-code-e09#3-large-bundles">Smaller Bundles</a></li><li class="bx--list__item"><a href="https://dev.to/this-is-learning/5-reasons-to-avoid-imperative-code-e09#4-unnecessary-complexity">Intuitive Dependency Direction</a></li><li class="bx--list__item"><a href="https://dev.to/this-is-learning/5-reasons-to-avoid-imperative-code-e09#bad-function-names">Easier and Better Variable Names</a></li></ul><p>The web development industry is inevitably transitioning towards more and more declarative code. But, it is happening very slowly, one layer of complexity at a time.</p>\n<p><strong>StateAdapt&#39;s purpose is to accelerate the industry transition to declarative code by providing tools that enable and simplify declarative code for every level of complexity.</strong></p>\n<h2 id="get-started">Get Started</h2>\n<p><a href="javascript:document.dispatchEvent(new CustomEvent(\'routeTo\', {detail: \'/angular/get-started\'})); void(0)">Angular</a></p>\n<p><a href="javascript:document.dispatchEvent(new CustomEvent(\'routeTo\', {detail: \'/react/get-started\'})); void(0)">React</a></p>\n<p><a href="javascript:document.dispatchEvent(new CustomEvent(\'routeTo\', {detail: \'/svelte/get-started\'})); void(0)">Svelte</a></p>\n<p><a href="javascript:document.dispatchEvent(new CustomEvent(\'routeTo\', {detail: \'/solid-js/get-started\'})); void(0)">SolidJS</a></p>\n<p><a href="https://dev.to/this-is-angular/progressive-reactivity-in-angular-1d40">Learn more</a></p>\n<h3 id="have-a-project-youd-like-to-see-implemented-in-stateadapt-open-an-issue-on-github">Have a project you&#39;d like to see implemented in StateAdapt? Open an issue <a href="https://github.com/state-adapt/state-adapt">on GitHub</a>.</h3>\n<h2 id="contribute">Contribute</h2>\n<p>Open an issue, request a feature, or ask for help <a href="https://github.com/state-adapt/state-adapt">on GitHub</a></p>\n'}}]);